# Reso Terminal Snake Game

Welcome to the Reso Snake Terminal Game! This is simple but with a lot of configuration opportunities for controlling game.

## Installation

1. Download or clone the game from the following GitHub repository: [Snake Game](https://github.com/resonanceIPC/ResoTerminalSnakeGame)
2. Open a terminal and navigate to the downloaded/cloned folder.

## Building the Game

1. Run the following command to build the game:

./install.sh

This will compile the game and create an executable file named "snake".

## Game Instructions

- To start the game, run the following command: 

./snake

- Use the arrow keys or the keys w, a, s, d to control the snake's movement.
(Note: Using the arrow keys may have some delay and may not work as smoothly as the keys w, a, s, d)

- You can customize the game settings from "Change parameters"
- Modify the desired parameters such as snake symbol, apple symbol, border symbol, and empty space symbol and so on.
- You can also change the colors of these symbols by modifying the corresponding color codes.
- You can also change height and width
- To exit the game, press the 'q' key.

Now you can enjoy playing the Resp Snake Game with your own properties!

